From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kaifeng Zou <winzkh@outlook.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Mar 2026 10:24:21 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] kernel/module: skip loading of oplus_secure_guard_new module to keep ksud compatibility

To ensure that kernel root implementations such as KernelSU can load
correctly on Oplus platforms with an unlocked bootloader, we ignore
the loading of the oplus_secure_guard_new module.

The load_module function is modified to intercept any module named
oplus_secure_guard_new early in the loading process. When detected,
the kernel skips the loading procedure and returns 0, effectively
disabling the oplus_secure_guard_new module while preventing
error escalation in user-space tools.

Signed-off-by: Kaifeng Zou <winzkh@outlook.com>
---
 kernel/module/main.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/kernel/module/main.c b/kernel/module/main.c
index ea1b4e1163898..6c4e0b4d3b502 100644
--- a/kernel/module/main.c
+++ b/kernel/module/main.c
@@ -2913,6 +2913,13 @@ static int load_module(struct load_info *info, const char __user *uargs,
        if (err)
                goto free_copy;

+       /* Skip oplus_secure_guard_new module load */
+       if (strcmp(info->name, "oplus_secure_guard_new") == 0) {
+               err = 0;
+               pr_warn("Blocking oplus_secure_guard_new module.");
+               goto free_copy;
+       }
+
        /* Figure out module layout, and allocate all the memory. */
        mod = layout_and_allocate(info, flags);
        if (IS_ERR(mod)) {
--
